title: Pistachio
description:
Pistachio

Pistacia vera

H30'


Deciduous. Native from Iran to central Asia. Spreading growth habit. Fruit is reddish, borne in heavy clusters. Edible, green or yellow seeds (pistachio nuts) are within hard shells.

title: Common Fig
description:
Common Fig

Ficus carica

H15-30'


Deciduous. Native to the eastern Mediterranean region. Large shrub or small tree. Trunk and branches become gnarled with age. Large, rounded leaves have 3 or 5 deep lobes. Edible fruit is ripe in summer. Drought tolerant when established.
